PACKAGES DOWNLOAD GUIDE

Installation via terminal
  You can use Command Prompt (CMD), PowerShell, Windows Terminal, VS Code integrated terminal, or PyCharm.

Install Python
  Packages work with Python version 3.10.X (Version 3.10.0 is recomended)
    Go to the official Python website: https://www.python.org/downloads/
    Look for Python 3.10.X (since your packages require 3.10).
    Click Download Python 3.10.X – this will download an executable installer (.exe).
    Open the downloaded file.
    Important: Check the box “Add Python 3.10 to PATH” at the bottom. This makes Python accessible from the terminal.
    Click Install Now.
    Wait for the installation to finish.
    Open Command Prompt (CMD) or PowerShell.
    Type:
      python --version
      You should see something like:
        Python 3.10.X

If Python is already installed
  To check the version, use the command "python --version"
    Example:
      Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.26200.7019]
      (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.
      C:\Users\norac>python --version  
      Python 3.10.11  

Update pip
  Use the command "python -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel"

Install MediaPipe
  "pip install mediapipe"

Install OpenCV
  "pip install opencv-python"

Install OSC
  "pip install python-osc"

To install them all at once:
  "pip install mediapipe opencv-python python-osc"

Verify package installation
  Inside any Python environment (IDLE, VS Code, PyCharm, etc.), run:
  import cv2
  import mediapipe as mp
  from pythonosc.udp_client import SimpleUDPClient
  print("OpenCV:", cv2.__version__)
  print("MediaPipe:", mp.__version__)
```  
